9:
Time for a little midnight sna—
Huh? What was that sound?
12:
Something's in the kitchen—No, someone!
Hey! Who's there?!
20: Th-this isn't what it looks like!
30:
So, I think you have some explaining 
to do.
36:
Let me get this straight: you thought 
we looked fishy and decided to tail us
—all the way to a different world—and 
now you're stranded.
37:
THEN, instead of asking for help, you 
stowed away until your hunger got 
the better of you.
38:
Not the type to look before you leap, 
huh?
43: Shut up! I said I KNOW alread—
50:
First things first, huh? Go ahead, eat 
up.
53: I-I don't need it! I don't accept charity!
58:
But you're okay with stealing?! 
You aren't paying for it either way!
61:
Besides, I had to make you SOMETHING
 for my own sanity. I can't believe you 
tried to eat meat from the icebox 
RAW!
64:
No more back-sass until you finish 
your dinner, mister!
67:
Tch. Acting so uppity... Who are you, 
my mom?
70:
Huh? This is—
This isn't bad...
73:
See, that's how meat tastes when you 
COOK it first.
76:
I know what meat tastes like, idiot. 
That's not what I meant...
79:
It just... kinda tastes like the stuff Mom 
used to make.
86:
I dunno, maybe. She died when I was 
little, so I don't really remember, but 
something about this tastes... 
familiar.
89:
I see... So you grew up with your Dad 
then?
92:
Hah! As if.
My father was a DEMON.
94:
That monster left us high and dry. 
I don't even know what he looks like, 
but I'll find him, and he WILL pay.
100: What about you, you nosy brat?
103:
My NAME is Alk.
But I guess I might be in the same 
boat as you. I'm not sure though, 
honestly.
109:
I have amnesia. I probably have 
parents out there somewhere, 
but I don't remember anything about 
them.
112:
Nothing? Not even a little?
Do you have any leads on where to 
look for them?
115:
Oh, I'm not really looking or anything. 
Even if I met them, they'd still be 
strangers to me, so...
116:
I guess we're all better off not knowing, 
right?
119:
You don't want to meet them? That's 
weird.
122:
Coming from someone who's trying 
to hunt down their father for revenge? 
Guess we're even.
126:
Yawn—
I have to be up early tomorrow for a 
quest, so I'm gonna call it a night.
130:
Oh, actually, why don't you come help 
out? I think this one'd be right up your 
alley, Asukirimaru.
133: Why should I do YOUR job?
136:
You said yourself you don't accept 
charity, so I'd say you owe us for the 
meal, at least.
143:
Hmph. Fine. If that sleepyhead needs 
a fighter, he's got Asukirimaru the 
demon-born—the best damn fighter 
there is!
